supported_functions: Splitting and Merging Strings and Arrays

Arithmetic.name: plus
Arithmetic.title: plus(a, b), a + b operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the sum of the numbers.You can also add integer numbers with a date or date and time. In the case of a date, adding an integer means adding the corresponding number of days. For a date with time, it means adding the corresponding number of seconds.

Arithmetic.name: minus
Arithmetic.title: minus(a, b), a - b operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the difference. The result is always signed.You can also calculate integer numbers from a date or date with time. The idea is the same – see above for ‘plus’.

Arithmetic.name: multiply
Arithmetic.title: multiply(a, b), a * b operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the product of the numbers.

Arithmetic.name: divide
Arithmetic.title: divide(a, b), a / b operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the quotient of the numbers. The result type is always a floating-point type. It is not integer division. For integer division, use the ‘intDiv’ function.When dividing by zero you get ‘inf’, ‘-inf’, or ‘nan’.

Arithmetic.name: intDiv
Arithmetic.title: intDiv(a, b)
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the quotient of the numbers. Divides into integers, rounding down (by the absolute value). An exception is thrown when dividing by zero or when dividing a minimal negative number by minus one.

Arithmetic.name: intDivOrZero
Arithmetic.title: Differs from ‘intDiv’ in that it returns zero when dividing by zero or when dividing a minimal negative number by minus one.

Arithmetic.name: modulo
Arithmetic.title: modulo(a, b), a % b operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the remainder after division. If arguments are floating-point numbers, they are pre-converted to integers by dropping the decimal portion. The remainder is taken in the same sense as in C++. Truncated division is used for negative numbers. An exception is thrown when dividing by zero or when dividing a minimal negative number by minus one.

Arithmetic.name: moduloOrZero
Arithmetic.title: moduloOrZero(a, b)
Arithmetic.description: Differs from modulo in that it returns zero when the divisor is zero.

Arithmetic.name: negate
Arithmetic.title: negate(a), -a operator
Arithmetic.description: Calculates a number with the reverse sign. The result is always signed.

Arithmetic.name: abs
Arithmetic.title: abs(a)
Arithmetic.description: Calculates the absolute value of the number (a). That is, if a < 0, it returns -a. For unsigned types it doesn’t do anything. For signed integer types, it returns an unsigned number.

Arithmetic.name: gcd
Arithmetic.title: gcd(a, b)
Arithmetic.description: Returns the greatest common divisor of the numbers. An exception is thrown when dividing by zero or when dividing a minimal negative number by minus one.

Arithmetic.name: lcm
Arithmetic.title: lcm(a, b)
Arithmetic.description: Returns the least common multiple of the numbers. An exception is thrown when dividing by zero or when dividing a minimal negative number by minus one.

Array.name: empty
Array.description: Returns 1 for an empty array, or 0 for a non-empty array. The result type is UInt8. The function also works for strings.

Array.name: notEmpty
Array.description: Returns 0 for an empty array, or 1 for a non-empty array. The result type is UInt8. The function also works for strings.

Array.name: length
Array.description: Returns the number of items in the array. The result type is UInt64. The function also works for strings.
